Description: This is New York State's premier early-stage venture forum where the best companies from across the state present to the investment firms.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Smart Start UNYTECH Venture Forum is an important showcase for the most promising technology companies and business innovators from throughout NYS and beyond. This is New York State's premier early-stage venture forum where the best companies from across the state present to the investment firms from New England to the Mid-Atlantic regions. Presented annually in the spring, companies are identified and vetted for participation in this event, and the resultant program features the state's best venture capital investment deal flow exposure across all market segments and technologies. Additionally, university spin-off companies are also presented as the up-and-coming pipeline of promising companies representing tomorrow's investment opportunities. SmartStart UNYTECH is the premier Upstate NY venture forum where VC firms look to see the best that the state has to offer for deal flow.  Now in its 13th year, SmartStart UNYTECH has to date highlighted 285 high-quality companies from throughout the state and beyond to the VC community, and their success speaks the quality of deal flow they select.  Of these companies, 64 have raised more than $500 M in equity financing, including more than $72 M directly attributable to their participation in the forum. In 2007, SmartStart was merged with UNYTECH, the Upstate University forum highlighting early-stage university spin-outs.  Additionally, this forum is marketed and recognized by many East Coast and Mid-Atlantic venture funds as the place to get Upstate NY technology deal flow.  They recognize each year some standout presentations with Best Business Presentation, Most Promising Technology and Most Likely to be Funded awards.   This unique event displays the very best early-stage companies from throughout the entire state of New York and beyond. Venture capital funds, seed investment funds and angel groups and investors can meet with and learn more about these company's teams, technologies and plans for succeeding in the marketplace. Additionally, experienced entrepreneurs are exposed to upcoming companies for their potential involvement, and many of the venture company service providers will also be on hand at this showcase event.   The SmartStart UNYTECH Venture Forum has tremendous support in the form of sponsorship from business, not-for-profit and government agencies, including statewide partners. For more information on organizations involved please visit the Advisory Committee Page.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: MyCreditVault provides a blueprint for a future of secure financial transactions. Our Mission is to end Identity Theft, as we know it, by giving consumers control. Turn Your Money ON/OFF In Seconds! With MyCreditVault, if thieves obtain your Social Security, bank account, credit or debit card numbers, unauthorized transactions will be denied approval. Finally, A Solution To End Identity Theft! Credit monitoring only tells you after theft may already occurred. Fraud alerts work better, but are temporary and can still allow fraud to slip thru. Credit freezes are effective but are difficult to set up and extremely inconvenient as they can take up to three days to turn on and off. MyCreditVault will work like a "Real-Time Credit Freeze" giving you 'lock & key' control over your credit files, credit/debit cards & bank account transactions. Important Questions About Your Credit 1. Is your good credit as valuable as your cash or is it more valuable? 2. If access to your cash requires a pin, why doesn't your credit? 3. What is stopping the protection of your credit as your cash? Identity Theft May Soon Be History (with your help)! An estimated 25 million Americans pay an average of $12.50 per month, for credit monitoring services. MyCreditVault believes many more would pay this monthly fee, for the peace in knowing their cash and credit accounts were more secure. Providing an improved service should increase adoption and even allow for increased fees. However, 100% of Americans could be covered for only $1/month at the same cost it now takes to pay for credit monitoring services for 25 million Americans. Albeit, for MyCreditVault to be fully embraced by banks, credit bureaus and credit monitoring service providers, the opportunity for increased revenues must exist. So how do we make MyCreditVault a reality? If those paying $12.50/month for credit monitoring services doubled to near 50 million Americans, or near 20% of all Americans, this would add about $3.75 billion in revenues. Javelin Research estimated fraud cost consumers and businesses $54 billion in 2009. CNN says that the healthcare industry alone is bilked of $100 billion/year, half being paid by Medicare with our tax dollars. In total, the estimated cost of ID theft to America is near $150 billion/year. If banks, credit bureaus and credit monitoring service providers were paid 50% of savings in the reduction of the financial losses due to Identity Theft and losses were reduced by 1/3, an additional $8.3 billion in revenues would be added. In total, new revenues for those protecting our financial accounts could rise $12 billion/year, thus replacing the estimated $6.6 billion/year in revenues banks lost from debit card processing, post-Durbin amendment, and add $5 billion, for those providing ID Theft prevention services. Plus America, would save about $33 billion/year and perhaps billions of hours a year! Even if this system cost $100 million to build, it makes the estimated $50 billion/year in healthcare and tax return fraud, paid for with our tax dollars, pale in comparison. If at all possible, tax dollars should not be used for development of this system. Banks and credit bureaus, the TRUSTED SERVICE PROVIDERS and GUARDIANS OF OUR CASH & CREDIT, should step up now to strongly support MyCreditVault! We need a credible and courageous media source to tell our story! WORKING TOGETHER, WE CAN END IDENTITY THEFT!

Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: [Lost Crates](http://www.lostcrates.com) is a subscription service that ships design-inspired goods to members’ doors each month or quarter, depending what they choose. Purchasers can choose between crates curated by the Lost Crates team or by its Partners in Design, and may sign up for as many different crate themes as they like. The company currently offers three crates curated by the Lost Crates team (Stationery, Petite Stationery, and Angie's Picks) as well as eight curated by its blog partners (Man Repeller, Joy the Baker, Gluten Free Girl, Inspired By Charm, Design Milk, Better Living Through Design, EcoSalon, and The Shiksa). Crates include items that complement each other and bring a little design into members’ daily lives. Subscriptions can also be purchased as gifts, and items from the different crates may be purchased a la carte in the Lost Crates Shop. Lost Crates was founded in March 2011 by Danny Levi and Millie Tadewaldt. In February 2012, the company, which was previously a stationery-only service, underwent a relaunch to feature more options and to appeal to a wider audience. In June 2012, the team welcomed Jack Wheeler as General Manager. Lost Crates is backed by Chicago-based venture capital firm and startup foundry [Sandbox Industries](http://www.sandboxindustries.com).

Description: My name is Nick Hawks, I am a Firefighter, Husband, and Father of three amazing children Nathaniel, Naomi, and Nygel!
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: My name is Nick Hawks, I am a Firefighter, Husband, and Father of three amazing children Nathaniel, Naomi, and Nygel! The oldest of the three is Nathaniel, and in 2011 he was diagnosed to be on the autism spectrum, and all I can say is, ""What an eye opening and humbling experience!"" He can push and test our cores but he shows a love like nothing I've ever known and he refuses to let labels and judgments stop him! He grows and learns more everyday! As any parents, but especially to the loved ones of an autistic person, we need breaks every now and then. For most, you just pick up the phone and call the neighbors 17 year old daughter and give her 20 bucks. For us, its quite different. I hear stories all the time of couple or family who haven't had a date night in YEARS. This is where we aim to give back. If you know the love and care that's required for our autistic friends and  family, then you know that most times, they cannot be left with just anyone. Its hard enough just to find a SAFE and reliable baby sitter, much less one with a background in autism care. Then comes Autism Sitter. We are developing a nationwide network of teachers, care-givers, other parents, and more who know how the puzzle works!  Help us grow this community and lets end the horror stories and abuse videos. Lets get proper care for our loved ones and enjoy ourselves every now and then! If you are unfamiliar with autism or the signs of autism, we welcome you to please visit: www.autism-society.org www.autismspeaks.org AutismSitter.com is, as far as I can tell, on its own. A quick google search of ""autism baby sitter"" brings up many many sites on how to find the right sitter, or basic keyword job sites, etc, BUT there are no actual sites that offer the service outright on a national framework level like us.  We need support for the following: Legal representation. Incorporation. Website domain and tools (we are currently using a sub-domain). Networking and Advertising.
